@WebApi_HostAddress = http://localhost:5125

### 1. LOGIN (Get the keys to the castle)
# @name login
POST {{WebApi_HostAddress}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "admin@crm.pl",
  "password": "Admin@123!"
}

### VARIABLE: Dynamic token extraction from the login response
@authToken = {{login.response.body.accessToken}}

### 2. GET ME (Check your current ID card)
GET {{WebApi_HostAddress}}/api/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

### 3. GET ALL PERSONS (Requires ReadOnlyAccess)
GET {{WebApi_HostAddress}}/api/contacts?page=1&size=10
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Accept: application/json

### 4. CREATE A NEW PERSON
# @name createPerson
POST {{WebApi_HostAddress}}/api/contacts
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "firstName": "Janusz",
  "lastName": "Kowalski",
  "email": "jan.kowalski@wsei.edu.pl",
  "phone": "+48 500 600 700",
  "birthDate": "1995-05-15T00:00:00Z",
  "gender": 1,
  "address": {
    "street": "Krupnicza 10",
    "city": "Krakow",
    "postalCode": "31-123",
    "country": "PL",
    "type": 1
  }
}

### VARIABLE: Extract ID from the newly created person
@newContactId = {{createPerson.response.body.id}}

### 5. ADD NOTE TO PERSON
POST {{WebApi_HostAddress}}/api/contacts/{{newContactId}}/notes
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "content": "Everything is working now!"
}

### 6. DELETE PERSON (Requires AdminOnly)
DELETE {{WebApi_HostAddress}}/api/contacts/{{newContactId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

### 7. NEGATIVE TEST: Attempt access without token
GET {{WebApi_HostAddress}}/api/contacts
Accept: application/json